Task
Number of zero elements in an array
Write a function countZeros that takes an array arr as an argument and returns the number of elements in the array equal to zero.
Example:
• the countZeros ([0, 2, -7, 8, 0]) function must return 2;
• the countZeros ([0, -1, -2]) function must return 1;
• the countZeros ([]) function must return 0.

Solution
function countZeros (arr) {
  let zeros = 0;
  for (let i = 0; i <arr.length; i ++) {
     if (arr [i] === 0)
    zeros ++
  }
    return zeros;
}
